article.description: Caprice Smith scored 17 points and Khara Smith added 16 to lead No. 15 DePaul to a 69-46 win over Pittsburgh on Sunday night in the Big East Conference tournament quarterfinals.
article.headline: DePaul's win sets up Big East semifinal vs. UConn
article.linkText: DePaul's win sets up Big East semifinal vs. UConn
article.story:
HARTFORD, Conn. (AP) -- Caprice Smith scored 17 points and Khara
Smith added 16 to lead No. 15 DePaul to a 69-46 win over Pittsburgh
on Sunday night in the Big East Conference tournament quarterfinals.

The third-seeded Blue Demons (25-5) will play Connecticut on
Monday. The seventh-ranked Huskies advanced with a 71-60 victory over Notre Dame
earlier in the night.

The sixth-seeded Panthers (19-10) earned their highest finish in
the league in 11 years. But they came undone Sunday night with a
season-high 23 turnovers and shot just 26 percent (12-for-47) from
the floor.

The Blue Demons scored 30 points of Pitt turnovers and dominated
from the perimeter. Caprice Smith's four 3-pointers were a career
high as DePaul made 10-of-23 from behind the arc. DePaul, one of
five former Conference USA teams to join the Big East this season,
is the only newcomer still alive in the tournament.

The Panthers were down just nine points at the half on Mallorie
Winn's runner with 2 seconds left and seemed to have the momentum
heading into the locker room. DePaul squelched that in a hurry with
four 3-pointers in the first 6 minutes and the Panthers never
recovered. The Blue Demons led by as many as 31 in the period.

Winn led Pitt with 12 points. Shavonte Zellous and Xenia Stewart
finished with 11 apiece.
